      <section eId="sec_311_6231">
        <num>311.6231</num>
        <content>
          <p>If, following the execution of an advance directive under , a court of the grantor’s principal domicile appoints a fiduciary charged with the care and protection of the grantor’s person, the fiduciary shall be bound by the terms of the grantor’s advance directive. If the advance directive designates a surrogate to make health care decisions for the grantor, the surrogate may continue to act.</p>
